don't have to pay two rents next month.

00:07:32.994 --> 00:07:35.330
No, mother, we're not moving.
Nope.Nope.

00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:36.957
Sorry, mum. Nope.Nope.

00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:41.836
Samantha, I have to go back to college
so I can make us a better living.

00:07:42.629 --> 00:07:45.298
With this job, I can't take care of us
the way I'd like to.

00:07:45.423 --> 00:07:47.592
I can't keep going this way.

00:07:47.717 --> 00:07:49.552
And grandma said she'd help us out.

00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:51.388
And it would be nice to be near her.

00:07:51.513 --> 00:07:52.514
Fine, mother.

00:07:52.639 --> 00:07:55.684
You can do whatever you want,
but we're not moving.

00:07:57.435 --> 00:07:58.937
What about our friends?

00:07:59.646 --> 00:08:04.985
Baby, we can email them or write.
We can come back to visit.

00:08:05.110 --> 00:08:06.528
And guess what.

00:08:06.653 --> 00:08:09.823
This place that grandma found us,
you'll each have your own room.

00:08:09.948 --> 00:08:11.700
Right?

00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:13.660
And there's a pool.

00:08:15.620 --> 00:08:18.623
Mum, do you still love dad?

00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:21.918
I still love your father,

00:08:22.043 --> 00:08:26.339
but that doesn't mean
it was healthy for us to stay together.

00:08:26.881 --> 00:08:31.344
What if after we move,
he's trying to find us and he can't?

00:08:31.928 --> 00:08:34.681
Oh, that won't be a problem.

00:08:34.806 --> 00:08:39.144
He can call grandma, and she'll tell him
or he can call information.

00:08:39.269 --> 00:08:41.146
We won't be hard to find.

00:08:41.271 --> 00:08:42.856
Is he still in Alaska?

00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:45.817
Well, that's what your uncle says.

00:08:45.942 --> 00:08:48.528
Probably taming polar bears
or something.

00:08:49.612 --> 00:08:53.199
Yeah.
Well, I hope they're taming him.

00:09:04.002 --> 00:09:05.837
Here. You wanna help me out?

00:09:05.962 --> 00:09:07.297
- Sure.
- Ok.

00:09:07.422 --> 00:09:10.842
Take this paint very carefully

00:09:10.967 --> 00:09:14.387
