Count down with me,
ladies and gentlemen!

00:29:53.667 --> 00:29:55.752
Nine! Eight!

00:29:55.877 --> 00:29:58.046
Seven! Six!

00:29:58.171 --> 00:30:01.341
Five! Four! Three!

00:30:01.466 --> 00:30:03.260
Two! One!

00:30:03.385 --> 00:30:07.264
Let's go! Woo-hoo!

00:30:12.144 --> 00:30:13.645
Thank you.

00:30:14.813 --> 00:30:16.231
Thanks.

00:30:21.778 --> 00:30:24.573
- All righty. There we go.
- Yay!

00:30:31.079 --> 00:30:34.124
No, no, no, no. Back up and take
a practice swing first, remember?

00:30:34.249 --> 00:30:37.085
Nice and easy.
Sweep the floor. Sweep the floor.

00:30:37.210 --> 00:30:38.962
That's good.

00:30:39.880 --> 00:30:42.674
Don't swing too hard, Randy.
He always swings too hard.

00:30:43.342 --> 00:30:46.094
Hey, all right! Very good!

00:30:46.219 --> 00:30:48.138
Back your feet up a little bit.

00:30:48.263 --> 00:30:50.766
Yeah, like that.
Now you're gonna hit it straighter. Ok.

00:30:51.767 --> 00:30:53.367
All right. Go up and hit it.
That's good.

00:30:53.393 --> 00:30:55.145
Nice slow swing
is gonna be better for you.

00:30:56.688 --> 00:30:57.981
All right!

00:31:00.192 --> 00:31:01.693
I don't know, man.
You must've been...

00:31:01.818 --> 00:31:03.862
See, your feet are too open, Randy.

00:31:03.987 --> 00:31:06.156
Nice and natural.

00:31:06.281 --> 00:31:08.116
Yes! Go!

00:31:08.241 --> 00:31:10.410
All right! Give me five.

00:31:10.535 --> 00:31:12.621
Good putt, son. Good putt.

00:31:12.746 --> 00:31:14.915
Did you see that, Randy?
That's the way to do it.

00:31:15.040 --> 00:31:17.542
All right. Birdie putt.

00:31:23.548 --> 00:31:27.052
Goddamn it. Son of a bitch.

00:31:28.011 --> 00:31:29.930
Get-get my clubs, would you?
Get the ball.

00:31:38.146 --> 00:31:41.858
This is just in case
we have guests this weekend.

00:31:43.360 --> 00:31:44.840
He always says that,

00:31:44.903 --> 00:31:46.446
but we never have a guest.

00:32:17.853 --> 00:32:19.855
Samantha, I think
I heard your dad pull up.

00:32:19.980 --> 00:32:21.820
- Oh, all right.
- You guys finish your chores?

00:32:21.940 --> 00:32:25.444
- Not quite.
- Just about.

00:32:26.570 --> 00:32:29.990
- How about the dusting, Sam?
- I haven't done that yet.

00:32:30.115 --> 00:32:31.867
Well, I saw you working
on your art project.

00:32:31.992 --> 00:32:34.095
I mean, you had time to finish
your little art project,

00:32:34.119 --> 00:32:35.805
but you didn't have time
to finish your chores?

00:32:35.829 --> 00:32:38.599
- I thought we talked about that.
- Dad, it's fine. I can finish the dusting...

00:32:38.623 --> 00:32:40.863
No, it's not fine, mindy.
You have your own chores to do,

00:32:40.917 --> 00:32:44.171
and Sam has hers to do.
Huh? It's simple.

00:32:45.297 --> 00:32:47.299
Poor choice there, Sam.

00:32:47.424 --> 00:32:49.259
And hurry up.

00:32:57.767 --> 00:32:58.852
Mason!

00:32:59.936 --> 00:33:01.771
Your dad's here.

00:33:04.357 --> 00:33:06.443
You guys aren't settin'
any speed records, are ya?

00:33:06.568 --> 00:33:09.738
What'd you do, get about half done?
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

00:33:10.655 --> 00:33:13.575
- So, did you finish?
- No.

00:33:13.700 --> 00:33:16.203
Is the job complete?

00:33:16.328 --> 00:33:18.914
So, what are you gonna
be doing tomorrow?

00:33:19.039 --> 00:33:20.540
- Same thing, right?
- Yeah.

00:33:20.665 --> 00:33:22.417
Ok. Go.

00:33:26.046 --> 00:33:28.340
- Bye, mum.
- Bye, babe. I love you.

00:33:30.133 --> 00:33:31.718
- Bye, mama.
- Bye, honey.

00:33:31.843 --> 00:33:33.345
Have fun with your dad.

00:33:33.470 --> 00:33:34.971
Just a minute, Mason.

00:33:37.182 --> 00:33:40.894
The boys didn't finish raking the leaves.
Samantha did not finish dusting.

00:33:41.019 --> 00:33:43.188
So tomorrow,
when they come home,

00:33:43.313 --> 00:33:45.833
instead of swimming and all the other
little stuff that they wanna do,

00:33:45.857 --> 00:33:48.026
- they're gonna do their chores, right?
- Right.

00:33:48.151 --> 00:33:50.820
Ok, guys, you had this conversation.
You understand?

00:33:50.946 --> 00:33:53.365
Tomorrow? Ok.

00:33:53.490 --> 00:33:55.450
Thank you. I just wanted you
to back me up on that

00:33:55.534 --> 00:33:57.553
so I'm not the only one
yelling at 'em all the time.

00:33:57.577 --> 00:33:59.538
Ok, I back you up.
You guys got that?

00:33:59.663 --> 00:34:02.123
We all agree. Everybody agrees, right?
Tomorrow, chores?

00:34:02.249 --> 00:34:05.168
Well, they don't hear it, you know?
Goes in one ear and out the other.

00:34:05.293 --> 00:34:07.546
But, dad, I mean,
dusting is pointless.

00:34:07.671 --> 00:34:09.591
It's not pointless.
You just don't like to do it.

00:34:09.631 --> 00:34:12.175
But I mean, who dusts anymore?

00:34:12.300 --> 00:34:14.052
You do when we ask you to!

00:34:14.177 --> 00:34:17.806
And don't... Olivia, don't let her back-talk
me in front of the other kids, please.

00:34:17.931 --> 00:34:19.766
- Thank you.
- Samantha, please.

00:34:21.643 --> 00:34:22.936
Whatever!

00:34:23.061 --> 00:34:25.647
Bye-bye.
Have a wonderful weekend.

00:34:25.772 --> 00:34:28.108
Ok. Bye, guys. Love you.

00:34:30.110 --> 00:34:31.945
I'm sorry,
but I thought we talked about it.

00:34:32.070 --> 00:34:34.340
You know? You have to draw a line,
you have to back it up.

00:34:34.364 --> 00:34:37.617
Ok. It's just you have
so many lines, bill.

00:34:37.742 --> 00:34:39.327
Everything's a line.

00:34:39.452 --> 00:34:41.621
- Hey, Randy. Hey, you guys.
- Bye. Bye.

00:34:41.746 --> 00:34:43.748
Hey, you two. How you doin'?

00:34:43.873 --> 00:34:45.709
- Shotgun.
- Ooh!

00:34:45.834 --> 00:34:47.669
Here, let me get this bag here.

00:34:47.794 --> 00:34:49.713
- You doin' ok, darlin'?
- Yeah.

00:34:49.838 --> 00:34:51.923
- All right. What about you, cowboy?
- Pretty good.

00:34:52.048 --> 00:34:53.633
Yeah?

00:34:53.758 --> 00:34:56.845
All right. Let's roll!

00:35:06.730 --> 00:35:10.025
- You guys ready for the big game?
- Yeah.

00:35:10.150 --> 00:35:12.027
Sam, who are the astros
playing tonight?

00:35:12.152 --> 00:35:14.738
- I don't know.
- The Milwaukee brewers, all right?

00:35:14.863 --> 00:35:16.299
Get to know 'em.
Get to hate 'em. Mase.

00:35:16.323 --> 00:35:18.116
How you been, huh?
How was your week?

00:35:18.241 --> 00:35:20.619
- Pretty good.
- Yeah? What you been up to?

00:35:20.744 --> 00:35:22.412
- Not much.
- No?

00:35:22.537 --> 00:35:23.977
You still hangin' with that kid Joe?

00:35:24.080 --> 00:35:25.749
- Yeah.
- He still your best friend?

00:35:25.874 --> 00:35:27.250
Yeah, I guess.

00:35:28.376 --> 00:35:30.337
Ok. How 'bout you?
How was your week?

00:35:30.462 --> 00:35:33.381
- Fine.
- What you been up to?

00:35:33.506 --> 00:35:34.799
Nothin' really.

00:35:34.924 --> 00:35:37.177
You, um... you still working
on that sculpture project?

00:35:37.302 --> 00:35:39.262
- Yeah. Almost finished.
- Yeah?

00:35:39.387 --> 00:35:42.015
- What's it of?
- Nothing.

00:35:43.892 --> 00:35:46.645
All right.
No, no, no, no, no, no.

00:35:46.770 --> 00:35:49.773
No, that is not how we are going
to talk to one another.

00:35:49.898 --> 00:35:52.776
All right?
No, I will not be that guy.

00:35:52.901 --> 00:35:54.778
You cannot put me
in that category, all right?

00:35:54.903 --> 00:35:57.697
"The biological father
I spend every other week with

00:35:57.822 --> 00:35:59.908
"that I make polite conversation,
you know,

00:36:00.033 --> 00:36:01.793
"while he drives me places
and buys me shit."

00:36:01.910 --> 00:36:03.912
No. Talk to me.

00:36:04.037 --> 00:36:05.664
Samantha, how was your week?

00:36:05.789 --> 00:36:07.549
"Um... I don't know, dad.
It was kinda tough.

00:36:07.582 --> 00:36:09.518
"Billy and Ellen broke up,
and Ellen's kinda mad at me

00:36:09.542 --> 00:36:11.711
"cos she saw me talking to Billy
in the cafeteria.

00:36:11.836 --> 00:36:13.439
"And remember that sculpture
I was workin' on?

00:36:13.463 --> 00:36:17.550
"Well, it was a unicorn, and the horn
broke off, so now it's a zebra." Ok?

00:36:17.676 --> 00:36:19.678
"But I still think I'm gonna get an a."
Right?

00:36:19.803 --> 00:36:21.721
Mason, uh... how was your week?

00:36:21.846 --> 00:36:23.446
"Well, dad, you know,
it was kinda tough.

00:36:23.556 --> 00:36:25.392
"Joey's kind of a jerk, actually.

00:36:25.517 --> 00:36:27.037
"He stole some cigarettes
from his mum,

00:36:27.143 --> 00:36:28.913
"and he wanted me to smoke 'em,
but I said no,

00:36:28.937 --> 00:36:31.248
"cos I knew what a hard time
you had quitting smoking, dad."

00:36:31.272 --> 00:36:32.774
How 'bout that? Is that so hard?

00:36:32.899 --> 00:36:35.068
Dad, these questions
are kind of hard to answer.

00:36:35.193 --> 00:36:38.154
What is so hard to answer
about what sculpture are you making?

00:36:38.279 --> 00:36:41.449
- It's abstract.
- Ok. Ok, that's good.

00:36:41.574 --> 00:36:43.678
See, that's... I didn't, I didn't,
I didn't know that.

00:36:43.702 --> 00:36:45.680
I didn't know that you were
even interested in abstract art.

00:36:45.704 --> 00:36:47.539
I'm not. They make us do it.

00:36:47.664 --> 00:36:49.874
But, dad, I mean,
why is it all on us though?

00:36:49.999 --> 00:36:52.001
You know, what about you?
How was your week?

00:36:52.127 --> 00:36:54.438
You know? Who do you hang out with?
Do you have a girlfriend?

00:36:54.462 --> 00:36:57.006
- What have you been up to?
- I see your point.

00:37:00.051 --> 00:37:02.721
So we should just let it happen
more natural, right?

00:37:02.846 --> 00:37:04.389
That's what you're sayin'?

00:37:04.514 --> 00:37:07.684
Ok. That's what we'll do,
starting now.

00:37:20.989 --> 00:37:22.824
Hey, check this out.

00:37:26.202 --> 00:37:30.123
That would be, uh...
That would be a magnificent owl.

00:37:30.248 --> 00:37:32.083
Cal/go atreus.

00:37:32.208 --> 00:37:33.394
What's that one? Look at this.

00:37:33.418 --> 00:37:35.503
- Whoa.
- What kind is that?

00:37:35.628 --> 00:37:37.964
That looks like a zebra longwing.

00:37:38.089 --> 00:37:39.966
- All right.
- Cool.

00:37:40.091 --> 00:37:43.178
This one's incredible.
That's the owl one, right?

00:37:43.303 --> 00:37:45.638
Yeah. Magnificent owl.

00:37:45.764 --> 00:37:49.058
I think he went pee-pee on you, bud.

00:37:50.685 --> 00:37:55.774
One, two, three, four, five.

00:38:16.503 --> 00:38:20.340
Ah! Ah! Get away from me!
Get away from me!

00:38:21.549 --> 00:38:23.384
Ah, ah, ah!

00:38:23.510 --> 00:38:26.888
Yo, mase, look at me here.
Make a diamond with your hands, right?

00:38:27.013 --> 00:38:28.723
Fingers and thumbs.

00:38:28.848 --> 00:38:32.143
Keep your hands soft. Hey, Sam.

00:38:32.268 --> 00:38:35.438
Very nice. That's how you wanna catch it,
just like that.

00:38:35.563 --> 00:38:38.250
Even when you're runnin', that's what
you're thinkin' about, that diamond.

00:38:38.274 --> 00:38:40.485
That diamond and soft hands.

00:38:40.610 --> 00:38:41.778
There it is.

00:38:44.864 --> 00:38:46.282
Down!

00:38:46.407 --> 00:38:47.659
Set!

00:38:47.784 --> 00:38:48.868
Hut!

00:38:50.537 --> 00:38:52.121
No, no, no, no, no!

00:38:52.247 --> 00:38:53.414
Dad! Dad!

00:38:53.540 --> 00:38:56.167
Don't let her get...
No, no, no, no, no!

00:38:57.418 --> 00:38:59.254
Let's go, Roger!

00:39:00.004 --> 00:39:01.422
- Dad?
- Get him out.

00:39:02.674 --> 00:39:04.968
Strike! That's it, Roger!

00:39:05.093 --> 00:39:07.762
- Yeah!
- Guy's incredible.

00:39:07.887 --> 00:39:10.306
He's unhittable this year.

00:39:10.431 --> 00:39:12.767
Now, just so you know,
what we're watching here is history.

00:39:12.892 --> 00:39:14.132
Now, you see this guy out here?

00:39:14.602 --> 00:39:18.356
This dude is like, 43 years old,
and he's strikin' out guys half his age.

00:39:18.481 --> 00:39:21.818
- Come on, Roger!
- This guy's era is 1.47, all right?

00:39:21.943 --> 00:39:22.944
Can you believe that?

00:39:23.069 --> 00:39:27.240
Now if the astros could just get a
few runs, maybe we'd win a game.

00:39:27.365 --> 00:39:30.785
Dad, do you have a job?

00:39:31.870 --> 00:39:34.122
Why would you ask me that?

00:39:34.247 --> 00:39:38.418
I don't know. Mum wanted to know,
and I didn't know what the answer was.

00:39:38.543 --> 00:39:40.044
All right, well, you can tell mum

00:39:40.169 --> 00:39:45.508
that I just happen to have passed
my second actuarial exam, all right?

00:39:45.633 --> 00:39:47.969
So... you tell her that.

00:39:48.094 --> 00:39:49.596
- How's she doing?
- Gmm.

00:39:49.721 --> 00:39:51.389
- Is she finishing school?
- Yep, all as.

00:39:51.514 --> 00:39:54.684
All as, huh?
Like mother, like daughter, right?

00:40:10.074 --> 00:40:13.578
He got that! It's out of here!

00:40:13.703 --> 00:40:15.538
Oh! Oh!

00:40:15.663 --> 00:40:19.667
- Yeah!
- Yay!

00:40:19.792 --> 00:40:21.252
Oh!

00:40:21.377 --> 00:40:24.547
Yeah! Mason! Yes!

00:40:26.341 --> 00:40:28.426
Yeah!

00:40:29.636 --> 00:40:31.220
Yeah!

00:40:32.055 --> 00:40:33.890
Yeah!

00:40:38.394 --> 00:40:40.980
- Hey!
- Yeah!

00:40:50.573 --> 00:40:52.241
-Hlfimmy - hey, Samantha.

00:40:52.367 --> 00:40:56.371
- Hey, what's up, Jimmy?
- What's goin' on, Mason, man?

00:40:56.496 --> 00:40:59.082
- Astros won.
- You went to the game?

00:40:59.207 --> 00:41:00.559
What, I'm the only one
with any arms around here?

00:41:00.583 --> 00:41:02.251
Nobody else can carry anything, huh?

00:41:02.377 --> 00:41:04.921
- Help their old man out?
- What you watching?

00:41:05.046 --> 00:41:08.549
Oh, come on, Jimmy, man! You knew
the kids were comin' this weekend.

00:41:08.675 --> 00:41:10.760
Can't you just help me out
a little bit, just...

00:41:10.885 --> 00:41:13.012
- I'm sorry, muffin.
- Don't "muffin" me, all right?

00:41:13.137 --> 00:41:16.933
Don't put me in that position.
I'm not your fucking Tony Randall.

00:41:17.058 --> 00:41:18.226
Dad, it's always a mess.

00:41:18.351 --> 00:41:21.104
It was not a mess this morning, ok?

00:41:21.729 --> 00:41:24.065
- I mowed the lawn.
- Oh, yeah? Great.

00:41:25.733 --> 00:41:30.321
Oh, come on, man! Turn this shit off.
Come on, give me that thing.

00:41:32.073 --> 00:41:33.908
- Did you watch the game?
- No.

00:41:34.033 --> 00:41:35.785
Lane won it
with a three-run homer.

00:41:35.910 --> 00:41:38.329
It was beautiful, wasn't it?

00:41:38.454 --> 00:41:42.375
Sam lost her mind.
She's a huge astros fan.

00:41:42.500 --> 00:41:44.168
Sure.

00:41:44.293 --> 00:41:47.547
♪ well, Saturday night
was a lunar eclipse

00:41:47.672 --> 00:41:52.468
