I can hear you!

01:43:14.772 --> 01:43:17.358
Well, I think that shotgun
should live at my house, huh?

01:43:17.483 --> 01:43:22.405
I don't think your mum would love that.

01:43:22.530 --> 01:43:25.700
Hey, look out, Sam.
Let me show you how it's done.

01:43:28.661 --> 01:43:30.996
Nice, dad.

01:43:31.122 --> 01:43:33.958
Still got the goods, hmm?

01:43:46.846 --> 01:43:49.181
How long you been in here, Mason?

01:43:49.306 --> 01:43:50.474
I'm not sure.

01:43:50.599 --> 01:43:52.351
I'm sure.

01:43:52.476 --> 01:43:54.478
All class.

01:43:54.603 --> 01:43:56.021
Did you complete your image diary?

01:43:56.147 --> 01:43:57.273
Not yet.

01:43:57.982 --> 01:44:00.443
Completed your digital contact sheet?

01:44:00.568 --> 01:44:03.446
Not quite. But, I mean,
it's not gonna take me long.

01:44:03.571 --> 01:44:07.324
"Not yet." "Not quite."

01:44:07.450 --> 01:44:09.869
Darkroom time is extracurricular.

01:44:10.453 --> 01:44:13.372
I mean, technically, you don't ever
have to be in here these days,

01:44:13.497 --> 01:44:16.000
and certainly not until
you've completed your assignments.

01:44:16.125 --> 01:44:18.919
- That's the deal.
- Sorry.

01:44:19.044 --> 01:44:20.838
I'm worried about you, Mason.

01:44:20.963 --> 01:44:23.716
- Why is that?
- I'll tell you why.

01:44:23.841 --> 01:44:27.678
The images you're turning in,
they're cool.

01:44:27.803 --> 01:44:30.723
You're looking at things
in a really unique way.

01:44:30.848 --> 01:44:32.516
Got a lot of natural talent.

01:44:33.309 --> 01:44:34.393
Thanks.

01:44:34.518 --> 01:44:39.774
Yeah, but that and 50 cents will just
get you a cup of coffee in this old world.

01:44:39.899 --> 01:44:44.695
I've met a lot of talented people
over the years.

01:44:44.820 --> 01:44:48.240
How many of them
made it professionally

01:44:48.365 --> 01:44:52.953
without discipline, commitment
and a really good work ethic?

01:44:53.829 --> 01:44:54.872
I can tell you.

01:44:54.997 --> 01:44:57.249
I can count it on two fingers.

01:44:57.875 --> 01:44:58.959
Zero.

01:44:59.084 --> 01:45:01.253
It's not gonna happen for you, Mason.

01:45:01.378 --> 01:45:03.047
The world is too competitive.

01:45:03.172 --> 01:45:06.509
There are too many talented people
who are willing to work hard

01:45:06.634 --> 01:45:09.637
and a boatload of morons
who are untalented

01:45:09.762 --> 01:45:11.430
who are more than willing
to surpass you.

01:45:11.555 --> 01:45:14.975
As a matter of fact, a lot of them are
sitting in that classroom out there right now.

01:45:15.100 --> 01:45:17.770
You know what they're doing?
They're doing their assignments.

01:45:17.895 --> 01:45:19.331
Which is what you're supposed
to be doing.

01:45:19.355 --> 01:45:22.399
But you're not, you're in here.
Now, why is that?

01:45:23.067 --> 01:45:25.110
- You special, Mason?
- No.

01:45:25.236 --> 01:45:28.489
But, I mean, the things you're talking
about, like work ethic or whatever,

01:45:28.614 --> 01:45:30.241
I feel like I do work pretty hard.

01:45:32.159 --> 01:45:35.246
I spend the whole weekend
taking pictures a lot of times.

01:45:37.248 --> 01:45:39.250
You like football, Mason?

01:45:40.793 --> 01:45:42.837
- Not really.
- Yeah, I know you don't.

01:45:42.962 --> 01:45:47.299
That's why I've just assigned you
to shoot the football game tonight.

01:45:47.424 --> 01:45:50.177
Ok? It starts at 7:30.
I want you to get there early.

01:45:50.302 --> 01:45:53.305
I want you to shoot a full card,
300 images. I want 'em downloaded.

01:45:53.430 --> 01:45:56.517
I want 'em sorted, and I wanna see 'em
very first thing Monday.

01:45:56.642 --> 01:45:58.143
Ok?

01:45:58.269 --> 01:45:59.895
Wanna know why I'm doing this?

01:46:00.980 --> 01:46:02.064
I guess.

01:46:02.189 --> 01:46:03.983
Who do you wanna be, Mason?

01:46:04.108 --> 01:46:06.861
- What do you wanna do?
- I wanna take pictures.

01:46:08.195 --> 01:46:09.530
Make art.

01:46:09.655 --> 01:46:11.949
Any dipshit can take pictures, Mason.

01:46:12.074 --> 01:46:15.369
Art... that's special.

01:46:15.494 --> 01:46:17.788
What can you bring to it
that nobody else can?

01:46:20.291 --> 01:46:21.792
That's what I'm trying to find out.

01:46:21.917 --> 01:46:23.919
Try harder.

01:46:24.044 --> 01:46:27.131
Hey, maybe in 20 years
you can call old mr turlington

01:46:27.256 --> 01:46:29.800
and you can say, "thank you, sir,

01:46:29.925 --> 01:46:32.595
"for that terrific darkroom chat
we had that day."

01:46:35.180 --> 01:46:37.600
Get back to class
and do your work.

01:46:50.070 --> 01:46:53.240
Hey, man.
You're walking a little funny.

01:46:53.365 --> 01:46:54.700
Fuck you.

01:46:54.825 --> 01:46:58.579
I'm just saying, you guys
were in there for a long time.

01:46:59.705 --> 01:47:02.541
Just hope he bought you dinner first.

01:47:17.014 --> 01:47:20.184
Mason, honey, come down for dinner!

01:47:21.352 --> 01:47:25.773
Samantha, you didn't post these pictures
and their descriptions?

01:47:25.898 --> 01:47:27.900
Come on. This auction
is gonna end on Sunday.

01:47:28.025 --> 01:47:30.110
Honey, you got to get those posted.

01:47:30.235 --> 01:47:32.154
Why are we even doing this?

01:47:32.279 --> 01:47:35.115
It's like an online junk shop.
I thought you had a good job.

01:47:35.240 --> 01:47:37.743
I do.
We're what you call "house poor".

01:47:38.577 --> 01:47:40.972
Everyone's gotta do their part.
Your brother took the pictures.

01:47:40.996 --> 01:47:42.998
You have to help.

01:47:43.123 --> 01:47:44.458
Who even buys this shit?

01:47:44.583 --> 01:47:46.502
Hey, Sam, watch your mouth, all right?

01:47:46.627 --> 01:47:50.047
Don't disrespect your mother.
You like a roof over your head, don't you?

01:47:50.172 --> 01:47:53.467
Yeah, and you like having electricity
so that you can charge your cell phone?

01:47:54.510 --> 01:47:56.971
I'm not even
gonna be here next year.

01:47:57.096 --> 01:48:01.934
I'm a senior.
I should be having fun.

01:48:19.702 --> 01:48:20.869
Nice nails.

01:48:22.037 --> 01:48:25.749
Yeah, some girl did that
in sixth period.

01:48:25.874 --> 01:48:28.210
You planning on keeping 'em?

01:48:28.335 --> 01:48:30.671
Until it comes off, I guess.

01:48:32.756 --> 01:48:36.593
Last summer it was the earrings,
and now the nails.

01:48:36.719 --> 01:48:39.555
You got a, uh... you got a purse
to go with all that?

01:48:39.680 --> 01:48:43.726
A lot of guys do that.
He's just trying to be cool.

01:48:46.145 --> 01:48:49.898
When I was in high school,
having a job,

01:48:50.024 --> 01:48:53.110
being responsible,
being able to afford a car,

01:48:53.235 --> 01:48:55.070
that was cool.

01:48:55.195 --> 01:48:58.949
Mason, honey, why don't you get you
and your sister some water?

01:49:31.315 --> 01:49:35.069
Hey, man, turlington says
to cut the artsy crap and shoot the game.

01:49:35.194 --> 01:49:37.863
So take your lens
and point it that way.

01:49:37.988 --> 01:49:40.741
- Jesus Christ.
- Also, we got a ride tonight.

01:49:40.866 --> 01:49:42.451
Mccormick's gonna take us
to the party.

01:49:42.576 --> 01:49:45.162
We're gonna head out after the game.
You're going, ok?

01:49:46.580 --> 01:49:48.540
Shoot the game.

01:50:00.803 --> 01:50:03.305
♪ long gone

01:50:06.141 --> 01:50:09.144
♪ oh, now she's long

01:50:11.897 --> 01:50:18.153
♪ yeah, now she's long gone
like Moses through the corn... ♪

01:50:19.696 --> 01:50:21.532
oh! First one.

01:50:21.657 --> 01:50:25.494
- What was that? What was that?
- That's what I'm talking about.

01:50:28.497 --> 01:50:31.166
♪ give me a cigarette and a beer

01:50:31.291 --> 01:50:35.712
♪ my wardrobe and stuff... ♪

01:50:41.385 --> 01:50:44.304
- Hey, what's up?
- Hey. How's it going?

01:50:44.429 --> 01:50:47.850
Pretty good.
How long have you been here?

01:50:47.975 --> 01:50:49.393
I don't know. A while, I guess.

01:50:49.518 --> 01:50:51.645
A while? Yeah.

01:50:54.773 --> 01:50:57.776
I just feel like there's so many things
that I could be doing

01:50:57.901 --> 01:51:00.654
and probably wanna be doing
that I'm just not.

01:51:00.779 --> 01:51:02.698
Why aren't you?

01:51:02.823 --> 01:51:05.409
I mean, I guess it's just being afraid

01:51:05.534 --> 01:51:07.953
of what people would think,
you know, judgment.

01:51:08.078 --> 01:51:10.247
Yeah.
I guess it's really easy to say,

01:51:10.372 --> 01:51:13.876
like, "I don't care what anyone
else thinks," but everyone does.

01:51:14.001 --> 01:51:16.128
- You know? Deep down.
- Exactly.

01:51:16.253 --> 01:51:20.174
I find myself so furious at all
these people that I'm in contact with

01:51:20.299 --> 01:51:22.885
just for controlling me or whatever.

01:51:23.010 --> 01:51:26.513
But, you know, they're not even aware
they're doing it.

01:51:26.638 --> 01:51:28.056
Yeah.

01:51:29.558 --> 01:51:33.312
So, in this perfect world
where no one's controlling you,

01:51:33.437 --> 01:51:34.646
what's different?

01:51:34.771 --> 01:51:37.733
- What changes?
- Everything.

01:51:37.858 --> 01:51:41.028
I mean, I just wanna be able
to do anything I want,

01:51:41.153 --> 01:51:42.654
because it makes me feel alive,

01:51:43.405 --> 01:51:46.825
as opposed to giving me
the appearance of normality.

01:51:47.451 --> 01:51:49.620
Whatever that means.

01:51:49.745 --> 01:51:52.539
I don't think it means much.

01:51:54.458 --> 01:51:56.793
You're kinda weird, you know that?

01:51:56.919 --> 01:51:58.128
Yeah?

01:52:00.214 --> 01:52:02.966
- Is that a compliment?
- I don't know.

01:52:03.091 --> 01:52:04.676
Do you wanna be weird?

01:52:04.801 --> 01:52:09.181
I mean, I don't wanna, like, scare kids
at the park or anything like that.

01:52:11.266 --> 01:52:13.268
I really like talking with you.

01:52:13.393 --> 01:52:17.731
I don't usually even try to, like, vocalise
my thoughts or feelings or anything.

01:52:18.649 --> 01:52:21.693
Just... I don't know.
It never sounds right. Words are stupid.

01:52:23.695 --> 01:52:25.948
So, why are you trying with me?

01:52:26.073 --> 01:52:28.659
I don't know.
I guess I feel comfortable.

01:52:30.035 --> 01:52:32.204
I'm glad.

01:52:35.707 --> 01:52:37.292
Hey, Jim.

01:52:37.417 --> 01:52:39.670
Uh... sorry I'm so late.

01:52:39.795 --> 01:52:42.798
What time were you
supposed to be home?

01:52:42.923 --> 01:52:45.926
I don't know, a while ago.

01:52:46.051 --> 01:52:50.764
A while ago like, 30 minutes ago,
an hour ago?

01:52:50.889 --> 01:52:53.392
Cos, truthfully, nobody even knew
where you were

01:52:53.517 --> 01:52:56.270
until your sister told us.
She's been home for a while.

01:52:57.729 --> 01:52:59.147
I'm sorry.

01:52:59.273 --> 01:53:02.025
Yeah, been hearing
a lot of that lately.

01:53:03.694 --> 01:53:06.530
See, but you don't actually care.

01:53:06.655 --> 01:53:10.242
You just kinda... kinda come and go
as you please,

01:53:10.367 --> 01:53:15.539
and you don't care if your mum's upset
or what time you gotta be home.

01:53:15.664 --> 01:53:17.207
Is that what's up?

01:53:18.417 --> 01:53:21.420
- I don't know what to tell you.
- Stop mumbling.

01:53:21.545 --> 01:53:23.547
You know, speak up.

01:53:23.672 --> 01:53:25.924
I can't understand a word
coming out of your mouth.

01:53:26.049 --> 01:53:27.884
It's just like...

01:53:28.010 --> 01:53:29.570
And I ask you questions,
and you just...

01:53:29.636 --> 01:53:32.472
Man, can I just have one day
where everybody isn't all over my ass?

01:53:35.475 --> 01:53:37.311
I'm up your ass?

01:53:39.062 --> 01:53:40.897
This is my house, all right?

01:53:41.023 --> 01:53:42.858
If you wanna live in my house,

01:53:42.983 --> 01:53:45.319
then you get home when you say
you're gonna be home.

01:53:45.444 --> 01:53:47.112
You know, Jim, you're not my dad.

01:53:47.237 --> 01:53:50.073
No, I'm not your dad.
You know how I know that?

01:53:50.198 --> 01:53:51.867
Cos I'm actually here.

01:53:51.992 --> 01:53:54.077
I'm the guy with the job,
paying the bills,

01:53:54.202 --> 01:53:57.205
taking care of you,
your mum, your sister.

01:53:57.331 --> 01:53:59.207
Huh? Huh?

01:53:59.333 --> 01:54:01.043
I'm that guy.

01:54:23.732 --> 01:54:26.651
- Morning.
- Morning.

01:54:26.777 --> 01:54:31.031
Hey, which one of you guys
used the downstairs bathroom last night?

01:54:31.156 --> 01:54:33.533
I don't know. I didn't.

01:54:33.658 --> 01:54:35.285
That tall guy, what's his name?

01:54:36.828 --> 01:54:40.332
- Phillip?
- Yeah, Phillip. He did it.

01:54:40.457 --> 01:54:41.625
Can Phillip read?

01:54:41.750 --> 01:54:44.437
There's a big sign on the door that says,
"do not use this bathroom. It's broken."

01:54:44.461 --> 01:54:46.630
I mean, how difficult is that?

01:54:47.506 --> 01:54:49.800
I-I don't know. I'm sorry.

01:54:54.763 --> 01:54:57.599
I think I'm gonna put the house
on the market.

01:54:57.724 --> 01:54:59.059
Why?

01:54:59.184 --> 01:55:02.062
This house is too big for us.
I mean, you're going to school eventually.

01:55:02.187 --> 01:55:04.314
It's too expensive. I'm done.

01:55:05.023 --> 01:55:07.143
Well, why did you even buy it
in the first place then?

01:55:07.943 --> 01:55:11.446
Because I really enjoy
making poor life decisions,

01:55:11.571 --> 01:55:13.990
keeping us on the brink of poverty.

01:55:14.950 --> 01:55:18.453
I mean, I've spent the first half
of my life acquiring all this crap,

01:55:18.578 --> 01:55:21.832
and now I'm gonna spend the second half
of my life getting rid of all this stuff.

01:55:21.957 --> 01:55:24.793
Really? Like what?

01:55:24.918 --> 01:55:27.087
Like... well, I got rid
of a couple husbands.

01:55:27.212 --> 01:55:29.332
Now I'm gonna get rid of a mortgage,
some maintenance,

01:55:29.423 --> 01:55:33.510
the tchotchkes,
the... the homeowner's insurance,

01:55:33.635 --> 01:55:36.763
the property tax, the plumbing.

01:55:38.807 --> 01:55:42.394
You know what? From now on,
I am gonna be mummy monk.

01:55:42.519 --> 01:55:44.688
Simple. Celibate.

01:55:44.813 --> 01:55:46.565
Don't be gross, mum.

01:55:48.984 --> 01:55:50.402
Fine.

01:55:50.527 --> 01:55:52.863
I'll be a poor whore
with a big house.

01:55:52.988 --> 01:55:55.157
Is that better?

01:56:02.164 --> 01:56:03.790
Mason.

01:56:03.915 --> 01:56:06.042
Mason, please, don't leave me
that dirty dish to wash.

01:56:07.252 --> 01:56:08.670
I do dishes all day.

01:56:08.795 --> 01:56:11.465
Well, great, honey.
Then you're a professional.

01:56:11.590 --> 01:56:14.426
Come on, you could do one or two more
for your poor old mum.

01:56:16.052 --> 01:56:17.888
Thank you.

01:56:40.827 --> 01:56:42.329
You want one?

01:56:42.454 --> 01:56:43.622
Fuck that.

01:56:43.747 --> 01:56:46.267
She didn't even touch 'em, seriously.
I watched her the whole time.

01:56:46.291 --> 01:56:49.544
Yeah, I bet you did watch her,
you little pervert.

01:56:51.755 --> 01:56:54.341
It's like we're on a date.

01:56:54.466 --> 01:56:56.134
Cheers.

01:56:57.093 --> 01:56:59.262
It's a night of romance.

01:56:59.387 --> 01:57:01.806
Yeah, except I'm not gonna kiss you.

01:57:03.058 --> 01:57:05.894
I will blow you though.

01:57:12.734 --> 01:57:14.069
Mason!

01:57:14.194 --> 01:57:17.531
- We are in the weeds out here.
- I'm going as fast as I can.

01:57:17.656 --> 01:57:19.741
Oh. Then I must be confused then,

01:57:19.866 --> 01:57:23.346
cos I just saw you chattin' it up with April
when I got a salad bar that needs a refill.

01:57:23.411 --> 01:57:27.332
I got a six-top, two four-tops I can't use
because they hadn't been bussed.

01:57:27.457 --> 01:57:29.793
Enrique is not here. I'm trying.

01:57:29.918 --> 01:57:32.254
Well, while you're tryin', we're dyin'!

01:57:32.379 --> 01:57:34.259
What... what am I supposed
to tell my customers?

01:57:34.339 --> 01:57:39.052
"Oh, I'm sorry that your table's
got dirty plates on it, but Mason's tryin'.

01:57:39.719 --> 01:57:41.137
"At least that's what he told me

01:57:41.263 --> 01:57:44.057
"after he was flirtin' with April
and eatin' your leftover shrimp."

01:57:44.849 --> 01:57:47.310
Now, it is a challenge
out there today, I know.

01:57:48.144 --> 01:57:50.480
But I wanna share something with you.

01:57:50.605 --> 01:57:52.607
I got you pegged
for fry cook this summer,

01:57:52.732 --> 01:57:54.818
and that's a lot more responsibility.

01:57:54.943 --> 01:57:57.988
It's also more money.
How's that sound?

01:57:59.030 --> 01:58:00.532
Good.

01:58:00.657 --> 01:58:05.161
I know you can handle that money,
but can you take the responsibility?

01:58:05.287 --> 01:58:08.123
I think you can,
because I believe in you.

01:58:08.248 --> 01:58:10.750
But I need you on the floor.
Now, leave the dishes.

01:58:10.875 --> 01:58:14.671
Giddyup. All right, come on.
Don't let me down.

01:58:18.675 --> 01:58:20.176
'Well, so it's... it's runnin' ok?

01:58:20.302 --> 01:58:22.012
'That alternator's
not messin' up anymore?'

01:58:22.137 --> 01:58:24.389
no, it's fine.
It's up for the trip.

01:58:27.100 --> 01:58:29.686
'Well, you gonna see your sister
when you guys are in Austin?'

01:58:29.811 --> 01:58:31.980
yeah, she said I can stay at her dorm,
which is cool,

01:58:32.105 --> 01:58:34.566
and I guess her roommate's
out of town, so it's no big deal.

01:58:34.691 --> 01:58:38.612
'All right, well, did you apply there yet?
Did you get that application in to ut?'

01:58:38.737 --> 01:58:41.906
- not yet, but sheena's pretty much in though.
- 'Yeah, right.

01:58:42.032 --> 01:58:43.718
'Well, if you know
that's where you wanna go,

01:58:43.742 --> 01:58:45.994
'you should probably do
that early acceptance thing.

01:58:46.119 --> 01:58:48.919
'I mean, seriously, let 'em know
you're a man who knows what he wants.'

01:58:48.997 --> 01:58:50.081
yeah.

01:58:50.206 --> 01:58:53.376
'A little decisiveness goes
a long way in this life. All right?'

01:58:53.501 --> 01:58:54.878
- yeah.
- 'Great.

01:58:55.003 --> 01:58:56.880
'And what about work?
How's that going?'

01:58:57.005 --> 01:58:59.507
uh... I don't know. It's all right.

01:58:59.633 --> 01:59:01.551
Today kind of sucked.
This guy didn't show up.

01:59:01.676 --> 01:59:05.347
But it's definitely an interesting
perspective on the world.

01:59:05.472 --> 01:59:07.223
People are slobs.

01:59:08.975 --> 01:59:11.311
'Well, when people ask me about you,
I say to them,

01:59:11.436 --> 01:59:15.732
"'oh, Mason, he's doing great.
He's got a job. He's really cleaning up."

01:59:16.566 --> 01:59:19.235
'All right, hey. Hey, say hi
to Annie and Cooper, will ya?'

01:59:20.528 --> 01:59:22.614
'say hi to your big brother.
Hey, big brother.'

01:59:22.739 --> 01:59:24.741
hey, Annie. Hey, kiddo.

01:59:24.866 --> 01:59:27.202
- 'Can you say bye-bye?'
- 'Bye-buh.'

