Should be some
pretty awesome stuff happening.

02:15:22.489 --> 02:15:26.243
Nah, dude. I'm going to this, like,
show with my dad in Austin.

02:15:26.368 --> 02:15:28.412
His friend's playing.

02:15:29.121 --> 02:15:31.123
God. Have fun with that, I guess.

02:15:32.958 --> 02:15:37.129
Fuck, there are so many cars here.
I don't wanna go in there.

02:15:37.254 --> 02:15:41.508
Dude, you will have so much fun.
Your family loves you.

02:15:41.634 --> 02:15:43.177
You're gonna have a swell time.

02:15:43.302 --> 02:15:45.596
Fuck you.
You're coming in with me.

02:15:45.721 --> 02:15:47.806
- Oh, no. Shit, no.
- Yes.

02:15:47.931 --> 02:15:50.017
Yes, you are. My mum loves you.
You have to say hi.

02:15:50.142 --> 02:15:51.644
Just...

02:15:52.227 --> 02:15:54.271
- Do you wanna hurt her feelings?
- Mm-mm.

02:15:54.396 --> 02:15:56.523
Well, then let's... let's go get 'em.

02:15:56.649 --> 02:16:00.527
Just for a second.
Just a second, seriously.

02:16:00.653 --> 02:16:03.906
You know, you're in sort of...
You're in enemy territory here.

02:16:04.031 --> 02:16:05.866
We're aware.

02:16:15.167 --> 02:16:17.336
Oh. Look who's here.

02:16:19.254 --> 02:16:21.090
Hey!

02:16:32.267 --> 02:16:33.519
Get a job!

02:16:36.522 --> 02:16:39.692
No, no, no, no, wait.
We're gonna take pictures. Put it back on.

02:16:39.817 --> 02:16:42.098
- Hey, can you get a camera?
- I got it. I got it.

02:16:42.194 --> 02:16:44.613
Congratulations, baby.
I don't know you, but congratulations.

02:16:45.364 --> 02:16:47.991
All right. Look here.

02:16:48.117 --> 02:16:50.119
- Smile.
- Here we go.

02:16:50.244 --> 02:16:51.578
Oh, that's a good one.

02:16:51.704 --> 02:16:54.164
And... good. Got it.

02:16:54.289 --> 02:16:56.458
Oh, we need...
Sam, where are you?

02:16:56.583 --> 02:16:57.793
- Samantha!
- Sam.

02:16:57.918 --> 02:16:59.628
And where's Mason senior?

02:16:59.753 --> 02:17:01.672
I'm feeling generous. Come here.

02:17:03.298 --> 02:17:05.634
Great. And...

02:17:05.759 --> 02:17:07.261
Beautiful.

02:17:07.386 --> 02:17:09.304
I'll email these to everyone.

02:17:10.639 --> 02:17:12.433
Don't even start.
Don't start. Don't start.

02:17:22.276 --> 02:17:24.945
Can't believe you guys came all this way.
It means a lot to me.

02:17:25.070 --> 02:17:28.907
Mmm. We wouldn't have missed it
for anything.

02:17:29.032 --> 02:17:31.034
I'm so proud of you.

02:17:31.160 --> 02:17:33.412
Congratulations.

02:17:33.537 --> 02:17:35.622
I'm really sorry
that Lee couldn't be here.

02:17:35.748 --> 02:17:37.267
- He's on his senior trip.
- No, no, no.

02:17:37.291 --> 02:17:38.792
- Tell him I said hi.
- I will.

02:17:38.917 --> 02:17:41.253
Abby, I didn't even recognise you.
How old are you now?

02:17:41.378 --> 02:17:44.006
- I'm 13.
- Wow.

02:17:47.342 --> 02:17:50.345
All right, let's top her off.

02:17:50.471 --> 02:17:51.889
You want some, doll?

02:17:52.014 --> 02:17:54.683
Um... sure. Yeah. Absolutely.

02:17:54.808 --> 02:17:56.008
I got you something.

02:17:57.728 --> 02:18:00.147
- What is it?
- That is a savings bond.

02:18:00.272 --> 02:18:03.275
That is worth something. It's better
than money. You just spend that.

02:18:05.194 --> 02:18:06.945
God, is that your mum?

02:18:07.070 --> 02:18:09.740
- Yeah, yeah. That's her.
- Wow.

02:18:09.865 --> 02:18:13.118
It'll be... three-second rule.
Put it on your plate.

02:18:13.243 --> 02:18:15.803
- Such a great dad.
- I know. I'm trying to help.

02:18:15.871 --> 02:18:18.152
Come here, you guys.
I wanna make a little toast to Mason.

02:18:20.626 --> 02:18:24.880
Now, Mason, I know you didn't really
wanna have a party today, but... we did.

02:18:25.005 --> 02:18:28.842
And you only graduate high school
once in your life.

02:18:29.635 --> 02:18:33.055
So I wanna celebrate you
and this next phase.

02:18:33.180 --> 02:18:34.973
And you're gonna learn
so much in college.

02:18:35.098 --> 02:18:37.778
You're gonna have so much fun.
You're gonna have inspiring teachers.

02:18:37.810 --> 02:18:41.230
You're gonna learn more
about your art.

02:18:41.355 --> 02:18:43.190
I love you, babe.
So proud of you.

02:18:43.315 --> 02:18:47.152
- To Mason.
- To Mason!

02:18:47.277 --> 02:18:49.196
- To Mason.
- Hear! Hear!

02:18:50.614 --> 02:18:51.949
All right, you're up, kid.

02:18:52.074 --> 02:18:55.160
Mm? Oh, uh...

02:18:55.285 --> 02:18:57.621
All right, uh... well...

02:18:57.746 --> 02:19:00.207
Mason, I'll make a toast
to the future.

02:19:00.332 --> 02:19:01.917
To your future.

02:19:02.042 --> 02:19:05.462
You know, it's been a little sketchy,
this end of the school year here,

02:19:05.587 --> 02:19:07.673
trying to figure out
what school to go to.

02:19:07.798 --> 02:19:12.886
Mason told me that, uh... he wanted
to get as far away from home as possible

02:19:13.011 --> 02:19:14.555
but still honour our agreement

02:19:14.680 --> 02:19:17.599
that we pay in-state tuition,
which I do appreciate.

02:19:17.724 --> 02:19:20.727
He's a prudent man,
and he's gonna have a great future.

02:19:20.853 --> 02:19:22.145
So... here's to you, buddy.

02:19:22.271 --> 02:19:23.522
- Whoo!
- Future!

02:19:23.647 --> 02:19:25.566
Congratulations.

02:19:27.067 --> 02:19:28.902
Mason Jr.

02:19:29.027 --> 02:19:32.990
High school graduate,
18 and straight.

02:19:33.115 --> 02:19:35.868
Just ignore him. My brother needs
to learn to pace himself.

02:19:35.993 --> 02:19:38.912
Well, I've not known you
as long as everybody here.

02:19:39.037 --> 02:19:43.709
But, uh... since I have known you,
you've grown a lot.

02:19:43.834 --> 02:19:46.420
And, uh... I-I-I don't know,
I'm proud of you.

02:19:46.545 --> 02:19:49.798
So if this photography thing
doesn't work out,

02:19:49.923 --> 02:19:51.925
you know, you always got a job.
Lose that earring.

02:19:52.050 --> 02:19:54.970
But, uh... you know, maybe
I can get you in front of house.

02:19:55.095 --> 02:19:57.347
All right. To you, buddy.

02:19:59.433 --> 02:20:02.269
- Sam, say something.
- Come on, Sam.

02:20:02.394 --> 02:20:04.646
- Um...
- Come on, darlin'.

02:20:05.188 --> 02:20:06.523
Good luck.

02:20:09.526 --> 02:20:13.196
- Yeah, Mason!
- Congratulations.

02:20:14.114 --> 02:20:15.657
Aw!

02:20:15.782 --> 02:20:18.160
So, you broke up with your girlfriend?

02:20:18.285 --> 02:20:20.162
Yeah. Yeah, just recently.

02:20:20.287 --> 02:20:22.456
- What's her name?
- Sheena.

02:20:22.581 --> 02:20:23.665
Sheena.

02:20:23.790 --> 02:20:26.293
She's gonna go to college with you?

02:20:26.418 --> 02:20:27.669
- No? Hmm...

02:20:27.794 --> 02:20:29.963
She's staying in this part of Texas.

02:20:30.088 --> 02:20:32.591
Oh, ok.
You need a ride to college?

02:20:33.383 --> 02:20:35.177
Oh!

02:20:35.302 --> 02:20:38.406
I just wanted to say hello before you got
outta here. I haven't gotten a chance.

02:20:38.430 --> 02:20:40.116
You guys met before, haven't you?
Annie and Jen?

02:20:40.140 --> 02:20:42.392
- Yeah, yeah, we met at, uh...
- Sam's graduation.

02:20:42.517 --> 02:20:44.853
- Oh, yeah.
- And with your little one. Where is he?

02:20:44.978 --> 02:20:47.230
- Oh, he's at home.
- Yeah, yeah.

02:20:47.356 --> 02:20:49.125
Remember, he was such a pain
at Sam's thing that, you know.

02:20:49.149 --> 02:20:50.901
I would love to see him.

02:20:51.026 --> 02:20:53.362
Well, we have a special weekend
this weekend, so...

02:20:53.487 --> 02:20:55.656
I'm so glad you found her.
I really am.

02:20:55.781 --> 02:20:58.033
You've got him
at a good time, I think.

02:20:58.158 --> 02:20:59.910
- I think so too.
- Yeah.

02:21:00.035 --> 02:21:02.204
- It's good to see you too.
- Nice to see you too, Jen.

02:21:02.329 --> 02:21:06.166
- I'm so proud of your boy.
- Yeah. Yeah, we all are.

02:21:08.377 --> 02:21:12.714
If you think she's a bitch now,
you should have seen her...

02:21:12.839 --> 02:21:15.485
You gotta remember,
you're going to college though, all right?

02:21:15.509 --> 02:21:18.345
And if you're anything like me
or your old man,

02:21:18.470 --> 02:21:20.555
you're gonna be pulling down
some serious wool.

02:21:20.681 --> 02:21:22.599
You're gonna be tapping
some masterful gap.

02:21:22.724 --> 02:21:24.494
You're gonna be doing
some good work out there.

02:21:24.518 --> 02:21:26.895
Think about it.
An awful lot of flowers in that bouquet.

02:21:27.020 --> 02:21:28.480
But you gotta do me a favour.

02:21:28.605 --> 02:21:30.607
You're gonna be vulnerable
this summer, all right?

02:21:30.732 --> 02:21:33.694
Remember to use protection
during breakup sex.

02:21:35.696 --> 02:21:38.281
This guy knows exactly
of which I speak.

02:21:38.407 --> 02:21:41.743
- Look what happened to him. Voila'.
- Steven.

02:21:43.954 --> 02:21:45.455
Cheers.

02:21:45.580 --> 02:21:47.958
It... it's not that simple.

02:21:48.083 --> 02:21:49.251
Four more years.

02:21:49.376 --> 02:21:51.378
Four more years.

02:21:51.503 --> 02:21:53.338
I'm just saying.

02:21:55.924 --> 02:21:58.176
Do y'all recycle? Should I...

02:21:58.301 --> 02:22:00.804
- I have one started there.
- Oh, yeah, right. Ok.

02:22:03.348 --> 02:22:08.020
Am I, uh... am I your only ex
at this party?

02:22:08.145 --> 02:22:12.149
Yes.
I'm not your only wife here though.

02:22:13.442 --> 02:22:14.860
Yeah.

02:22:17.195 --> 02:22:20.365
Can you believe
they're both out of high school?

02:22:22.367 --> 02:22:23.702
No, I can't.

02:22:25.662 --> 02:22:29.666
You did a-a great job
with both of them, by the way.

02:22:29.791 --> 02:22:32.044
Thanks for saying that.

02:22:32.169 --> 02:22:33.837
I never thought
I'd hear you say that.

02:22:33.962 --> 02:22:36.715
Well, it's true. Thank you.

02:22:38.425 --> 02:22:39.968
You're doing it all over again, huh?

02:22:40.093 --> 02:22:42.512
I know. I know, right?

02:22:42.637 --> 02:22:46.433
It's gonna be, uh... 15 years
till I have an empty nest.

02:22:46.558 --> 02:22:48.310
Hmm.

02:22:48.435 --> 02:22:51.313
But hey, I'd love to pitch in,
help with this, if I could.

02:22:51.438 --> 02:22:53.273
It's so great that you did this.

02:22:53.398 --> 02:22:57.235
Can I just give you a little...
I'd appreciate it if I could.

02:22:57.360 --> 02:22:58.945
Sure, yeah.

02:22:59.071 --> 02:23:00.447
But I don't have any cash.

02:23:00.572 --> 02:23:03.992
No, it's in Annie's purse.
I'll be right back.

02:23:11.249 --> 02:23:13.919
So it sucks. I mean,
the guy's a college lacrosse player.

02:23:14.044 --> 02:23:17.881
- I mean, what are you gonna do?
- She didn't even like sports.

02:23:18.006 --> 02:23:20.509
- You want a beer?
- No, that's all right.

02:23:20.634 --> 02:23:22.469
- You can have one.
- It's all right.

02:23:22.594 --> 02:23:24.596
Yeah, well, for what it's worth,

02:23:24.721 --> 02:23:28.225
we've all been through the exact
same thing at one point or another.

02:23:29.559 --> 02:23:32.145
It's not the same though.
I mean, you never got to know her.

02:23:32.270 --> 02:23:35.440
No, I know, I know.
It's not the same.

02:23:35.565 --> 02:23:37.567
I just don't know
what I did wrong.

02:23:37.692 --> 02:23:41.613
Hey, Jimmy. Hey, man. Hey.

02:23:42.197 --> 02:23:43.490
Hey, Mason.

02:23:43.615 --> 02:23:46.034
We're up here, uh... raiding
the green room. Hope that's ok.

02:23:46.159 --> 02:23:48.370
- That's totally cool.
- All right.

02:23:51.623 --> 02:23:53.667
Wow. Is that m.J.?

02:23:53.792 --> 02:23:55.293
Uh-huh. Right?

02:23:55.418 --> 02:23:57.212
Unbelievable.

02:23:58.088 --> 02:24:00.674
Well, we just decided to come
a little early, check you out.

02:24:00.799 --> 02:24:02.985
That's cool, man. Let me finish up.
I'll be up in a minute.

02:24:03.009 --> 02:24:05.804
All right. All right. I guarantee you,
you didn't do anything wrong.

02:24:06.513 --> 02:24:08.515
These high school love things,
they never work out.

02:24:08.640 --> 02:24:09.808
Here, come here.

02:24:09.933 --> 02:24:12.936
I mean, everybody's
just changing so much, you know?

02:24:13.061 --> 02:24:16.731
The odds of two young people
staying on the same wavelength are...

02:24:16.857 --> 02:24:19.276
- Yeah, but still...
- Look, and I also guarantee you

02:24:19.401 --> 02:24:22.988
that every day of your life
that you spend crying over some silly girl

02:24:23.113 --> 02:24:25.866
is a complete waste of time.

02:24:25.991 --> 02:24:29.744
She wasn't a silly girl though.
I mean, she's a serious person.

02:24:29.870 --> 02:24:31.538
I really thought we were...

02:24:31.663 --> 02:24:33.999
- What?
- I don't know.

02:24:34.124 --> 02:24:36.209
Here's the truth.

02:24:36.334 --> 02:24:38.920
Women are never satisfied, ok?

02:24:39.045 --> 02:24:42.382
They're always looking to potentially
trade up, and that's, I'm sorry to say,

02:24:42.507 --> 02:24:44.827
what I think has happened to you,
my fine-feathered friend.

02:24:44.885 --> 02:24:46.303
What does that even mean?

02:24:46.428 --> 02:24:49.973
It means don't hand over the controls
to your self-esteem to Sheila.

02:24:50.098 --> 02:24:51.266
- Sheena.
- All right?

02:24:51.391 --> 02:24:53.226
It means you are responsible
for you.

02:24:53.351 --> 02:24:55.770
Not your girlfriend,
not your mum, not me.

02:24:55.896 --> 02:24:58.732
You. And if you truly
take care of you,

02:24:58.857 --> 02:25:01.610
you will be amazed
at how much girls like sheena

02:25:01.735 --> 02:25:04.237
start lining up at your front door.

02:25:04.863 --> 02:25:05.947
Great.

02:25:06.072 --> 02:25:09.032
Yeah, you know, you just gotta separate
yourself from the pack in some way.

02:25:09.117 --> 02:25:11.119
Excel at something, you know,

02:25:11.244 --> 02:25:12.844
and then you have
your pick of the litter

02:25:12.954 --> 02:25:15.457
when them front-running hussies
start sniffing around.

02:25:15.582 --> 02:25:18.001
So what you're saying is
I should take up lacrosse.

02:25:18.126 --> 02:25:21.796
Exactly. Or you could,
you know, start a band.

02:25:21.922 --> 02:25:24.257
Worked for me a long time ago.

02:25:24.382 --> 02:25:25.884
I think it's still working for Jimmy.

02:25:26.009 --> 02:25:28.511
Or you just keep taking pictures.

02:25:29.054 --> 02:25:31.139
She hated the pictures I took of her.

02:25:31.264 --> 02:25:33.266
All right.
I'm sick to death of her, ok?

02:25:33.391 --> 02:25:35.828
I only met her a few times.
And, yes, she was cute, all right?

02:25:35.852 --> 02:25:39.439
But truth be told,
I always thought she was a little bit,

02:25:39.564 --> 02:25:41.566
you know,
a little bit too square for you.

02:25:41.691 --> 02:25:44.110
You know, not quite the same vibe.

02:25:44.236 --> 02:25:47.072
- You really thought that?
- On some subtle, lower level.

02:25:47.697 --> 02:25:51.368
I mean, uh... I wasn't surprised
when it turned out

02:25:51.493 --> 02:25:55.163
she was interested in some
knucklehead lacrosse player, ok?

02:25:55.288 --> 02:25:58.959
I mean, the bottom line is
it's all timing with these things.

02:25:59.084 --> 02:26:00.502
Yeah.

02:26:00.627 --> 02:26:02.796
I mean, uh... take your mum and me.

02:26:02.921 --> 02:26:06.758
You know, I think I've probably turned
into the boring castrated guy

02:26:06.883 --> 02:26:09.886
she wanted me to be
15, 20 years ago, you know?

02:26:10.011 --> 02:26:12.198
I mean, I'm not saying she was wrong
to be pissed. I'm not.

02:26:12.222 --> 02:26:15.892
I'm just saying that she could've been a
little more patient, a little more forgiving.

02:26:16.017 --> 02:26:18.603
Would've saved me that parade
of drunken assholes.

02:26:27.946 --> 02:26:29.114
So what's the point?

02:26:30.824 --> 02:26:31.908
Of what?

02:26:32.993 --> 02:26:35.412
I don't know. Any of this.
Everything.

02:26:36.663 --> 02:26:38.581
Everything?

02:26:38.707 --> 02:26:41.710
What's the point?
I mean, I sure as shit don't know.

02:26:41.835 --> 02:26:44.045
Neither... neither does
anybody else, ok?

02:26:44.170 --> 02:26:47.257
We're all just... winging it, you know?

02:26:47.382 --> 02:26:49.182
I mean, the good news
is you're feeling stuff.

02:26:50.093 --> 02:26:52.095
You know?
And you gotta hold on to that.

02:26:52.220 --> 02:26:55.473
You do. I mean, you get older
and you don't feel as much.

02:26:55.598 --> 02:26:57.434
Your skin gets tougher.

02:26:57.559 --> 02:26:59.060
The point is those pictures you took.

02:26:59.185 --> 02:27:03.315
Thousands of submissions
from all over the state, and you won.

02:27:03.440 --> 02:27:05.608
Well, I got silver.

02:27:05.734 --> 02:27:07.586
- And nine other people did too.
- I'm gonna kill you.

02:27:07.610 --> 02:27:11.448
I'm trying to tell you that I believe in
you, Mason. I think you're really special.

02:27:11.573 --> 02:27:13.908
And if some girl doesn't see that,
then fuck her, you know?

02:27:15.660 --> 02:27:18.997
Hey, this next one goes out
to a young man in the house.

02:27:19.122 --> 02:27:22.083
- Whoo-hoo!
- Known him since he was just a small boy.

02:27:22.208 --> 02:27:26.755
Now he's all graduated from high school
and making me feel old.

02:27:28.423 --> 02:27:30.842
Happy high school graduation, Mason.

02:27:58.119 --> 02:27:59.537
Thank you.

02:28:00.246 --> 02:28:02.123
Ok, guys, let's be clear.

02:28:02.248 --> 02:28:03.917
I'm gonna break this
into four categories.

02:28:04.042 --> 02:28:07.462
One, anything you wanna keep from
your childhood and you're taking with you.

02:28:07.587 --> 02:28:09.756
Two, throwing away.

02:28:09.881 --> 02:28:11.716
Three, donating.

02:28:11.841 --> 02:28:15.845
Four, whatever you wanna try to sell
at the garage sale next weekend.

02:28:15.970 --> 02:28:18.056
Whatever we don't sell,
we're donating.

02:28:18.681 --> 02:28:22.560
Doesn't the apartment have,
like, an attic or storage or something?

02:28:22.685 --> 02:28:25.688
No. You're missing the point.

02:28:25.814 --> 02:28:28.441
We're not gonna drag a bunch of crap
to mum's tiny apartment.

02:28:29.067 --> 02:28:31.069
Can't believe we're moving again.

02:28:31.194 --> 02:28:33.947
No, I'm moving.
You moved two years ago.

02:28:34.072 --> 02:28:37.575
You have an apartment in Austin.
Mason is moving in the fall.

02:28:38.118 --> 02:28:39.619
I'm done.

02:28:39.744 --> 02:28:41.913
This will be great for me.
I'll have all these options.

02:28:42.038 --> 02:28:43.540
I can take a sabbatical.

02:28:43.665 --> 02:28:45.959
I can get some writing done,
try to get published.

02:28:46.084 --> 02:28:48.086
What about Christmas though?
What are we gonna do?

02:28:48.211 --> 02:28:50.046
I'm not sharing a room with him.

02:28:50.171 --> 02:28:53.967
One of you will sleep on the couch,
